,"rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3210,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/05\/16\/ghusl-before-jumuah\/","url_meta":{"origin":15807,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Ghusl: Perform ritual bath before Friday prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 16, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cTaking a bath on Friday is a duty upon every person who has reached the age of puberty.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 839,\u00a0S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 846 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15799,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/23\/attend-sermon-quietly\/","url_meta":{"origin":15807,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Jumuah: Minor sins forgiven until next Friday","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 23, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever performs ablution in the best manner, comes to Friday prayer, and listens while remaining quiet, his\u00a0sins will be forgiven until the next Friday and an additional three days, but whoever plays with pebbles has behaved\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25635,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/19\/ghusl-once-seven-days\/","url_meta":{"origin":15807,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ghusl: Take a bath at least once a week","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 19, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIt is a duty for Allah upon every Muslim to perform a ritual bath at least once every seven days, washing his head and his body.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 856, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 849 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11859,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/29\/none-maintain-wudu-believer\/","url_meta":{"origin":15807,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: None maintains ablution but a believer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 29, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Thawban reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cRemain upright, though you cannot encompass it entirely. Know that the best of your good deeds is prayer and that none can preserve his ablution but a believer.\u201d Source: Sunan Ibn Ma\u0304jah 277 Grade:\u00a0Sahih (authentic) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\